description._content:
We were supposed to go for two days and two nights. However, we missed the last boat on our first day and had to stay at a resort in the mainland, near the port. Blame the huge waves for that. 

We were booked last year, months before the devastating storm hit the country. My group woke up at four am just to make sure we can go to the island as early as possible. We were able to go there, but not without a fight. The waves had the subtlety of a rock concert. 

Once on the island, however, we forgot our body pains to find the most beautiful island paradise, comparable with the best in the country. The photo captures the inhospitable beauty of the Bantayan island in Cebu. This is the best I can do. 

Jan 24, 2014, Pentax K-x, SMC Pentax-M 50mm f/1.4
